---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Nutritionists & Dietitians — Client Testimonials That Grow Your Practice | SocialProof" description="Nutritionists and dietitians: clients choose based on trust and results. SocialProof helps you collect and display client testimonials that showcase real transformations and build your waitlist.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Nutritionists &amp; Dietitians
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Nutrition is deeply personal — clients are trusting you with their health, energy, and relationship with food. Before booking, they need to believe you can actually help them. Client testimonials showing real results are the most persuasive thing you can put on your website.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why testimonials drive practice growth</h2>
      <p>People seeking nutrition guidance have usually tried and failed at multiple approaches before. They're skeptical and looking for someone who "gets" their specific situation. A testimonial from someone who had the same struggle — IBS, pre-diabetes, post-partum nutrition, athletic performance — lands far more powerfully than any credentials or service description.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">SocialProof helps you collect those stories from satisfied clients and display them on your website where prospective clients are making their decision.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What converts in nutrition testimonials</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Specific results:</strong> "Lost 18 pounds in 4 months without feeling deprived. My energy is completely different."</li>
        <li><strong>Condition-specific wins:</strong> "My A1C dropped from 7.2 to 5.9 after three months of working together."</li>
        <li><strong>Approach validation:</strong> "She didn't give me a generic plan — everything was built around my schedule, my food preferences, my life."</li>
        <li><strong>Long-term impact:</strong> "I finally understand why I was eating the way I was. The habits have stuck two years later."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How it works</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li>After a successful client milestone, send a SocialProof link via your existing client communication</li>
        <li>Client submits a testimonial — no account, just a simple form</li>
        <li>You approve it and it appears on your site immediately</li>
        <li>Prospective clients find your website and read about real outcomes before booking a discovery call</li>
      </ol>

      <div style="background:#f8f9fa;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget</h3>
        <p style="color:#555;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Start collecting and displaying client success stories today. No credit card required.</p>
        <a href="https://socialproof.dev/signup" style="display:inline-block;background:#0070f3;color:#fff;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:8px;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Start free</a>
      </div>

      <section style="margin-top:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
          "@context": "https://schema.org",
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "How do I collect testimonials from nutrition clients without being pushy?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "The key is timing and framing. Ask after a clear win — a milestone reached, a goal achieved, or a meaningful check-in where they express gratitude. A simple 'Would you be open to sharing a few words about your experience? It really helps others in similar situations find me' works naturally. SocialProof makes the submission frictionless — one link, no account required."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Are there HIPAA considerations with nutrition client testimonials?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Testimonials that clients submit voluntarily about their own experience are generally not subject to HIPAA — the client is disclosing their own information. However, always let clients know what they're submitting and where it will be displayed. Never include any client details that they didn't include themselves."
              }
            }
          ]
        })}>
        </script>

        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">How do I collect testimonials without being pushy?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Ask after a clear win — a milestone reached or a goal achieved. A simple "Would you share a few words? It helps others in similar situations find me" works naturally. SocialProof makes the submission frictionless — one link, no account required.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Are there HIPAA considerations with client testimonials?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Testimonials clients submit voluntarily about their own experience are generally not subject to HIPAA. Always let clients know what they're submitting and where it will be displayed. Never include any client details they didn't provide themselves.</p>
        </details>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
